obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21036)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21036&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Warehousing`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 2007.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . 25th October, 2010, vide notification No. S.O. 2613(E), dated 21st October, 2010, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21037)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21037&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "accreditation agency" means an agency, whatever be its constitution, registered with the`
  line `Authority under section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) "actionable claim" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 3 of the Transfer of`
  line `Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882);`
  line
  line `(c) "Authority" means the Warehousing Development and Regulatory Authority established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(d) "depositor" means a person who delivers goods to the warehouseman for storage;`
  line
  line `(e) "endorsee" means the person to whom the warehouse receipt is negotiated;`
  line
  line `(f) "endorsement" means signing on the warehouse receipt by the depositor or holder of the`
  line `warehouse receipt for the purpose of its negotiation;`
  line
  line `(g) "electronic form", with reference to information, means any information generated, sent,`
  line `received or stored in media, magnetic, optical, computer memory, microfilm, computer generated`
  line `micro fiche or similar device;`
  line
  line `(h) "fungible goods" means any goods of which any unit is, by nature or usage of trade, the`
  line `equivalent of any other like unit and are received by a warehouseman as fungible goods;`
  line
  line `(i) "goods" means all tangible movable goods (other than actionable claims, money and`
  line `securities), whether fungible or not;`
  line
  line `(j) "grade" means the quality standard of any goods as notified as grade designation by the`
  line `Central Government under the Agricultural Produce (Grading and Marking) Act, 1937 (1 of 1937) or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(k) "holder" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a negotiable warehouse receipt, a person who is in possession of such receipt`
  line `and a right to goods endorsed on it; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a non-negotiable warehouse receipt, a person named in it as the person to`
  line `whom the goods are to be delivered or the assignee of that person;`
  line
  line `(l) "member" means a member of the Authority and includes its Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(m) "negotiable warehouse receipt" means a warehouse receipt under which the goods`
  line `represented therein are deliverable to the depositor or order, the endorsement of which has the effect`
  line `of transfer of goods represented thereby and the endorsee for which takes a good title;`
  line
  line `(n) "non-negotiable warehouse receipt" means a warehouse receipt other than a negotiable`
  line `warehouse receipt;`
  line
  line `(o) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(p) "person" includes a firm, co-operative society or any association or body of persons, whether`
  line `incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(q) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) "warehouse" means any premises (including any protected place) conforming to all the`
  line `requirements including manpower specified by the Authority by regulations wherein the`
  line `warehouseman takes custody of the goods deposited by the depositor and includes a place of storage`
  line `of goods under controlled conditions of temperature and humidity;`
  line
  line `(t) "warehousing business" means the Business of maintaining warehouses in storage of goods`
  line `and issuing negotiable warehouse receipts;`
  line
  line `(u) "warehouse receipt" means an acknowledgement in writing or in electronic form issued by a`
  line `warehouseman or his duly authorised representative (including depository by whatever name called)`
  line `of the receipt for storage of goods not owned by the warehouseman;`
  line
  line `(v) "warehouseman" means any person who is granted a certificate of registration in respect of`
  line `any warehouse or warehouses by the Authority or an accreditation agency for carrying on the`
  line `business of warehousing.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21038)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Requirement of registration for warehouses issuing negotiable warehouse receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21038&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `person shall commence or carry on the warehousing business unless he has obtained a registration`
  line `certificate in respect of the concerned warehouse or warehouses granted by the Authority under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person carrying on the warehousing business immediately before the commencement`
  line `of this Act shall be allowed to carry on such business, in case he has made an application for registration`
  line `within thirty days from the date of such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such registration shall be required for warehouses which do not propose to`
  line `issue negotiable warehouse receipt.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that a warehouse registered under this`
  line `Act shall also be eligible to issue non-negotiable warehouse receipts.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Authority may, subject to such`
  line `regulations and guidelines issued by it, authorise any person registered under section 5 as an accreditation`
  line `agency to issue certificate of accreditation to any person for carrying on the business of warehousing`
  line `issuing negotiable warehouse receipts.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21039)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Registration of warehousemen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21039&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desirous of commencing or carrying on the`
  line `business of maintaining a warehouse issuing negotiable warehouse receipts may make an application to`
  line `the Authority for registration in respect of one or more warehouses owned or occupied by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and manner and shall`
  line `be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority may, after such enquiry and subject to such terms and conditions as it thinks fit,`
  line `grant a certificate of registration of the warehouse in the prescribed form and bearing a registration`
  line `number to the applicant authorising him to carry on the business of maintaining a warehouse or`
  line `warehouses and to issue negotiable warehouse receipts.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority may not grant a certificate of registration under this section unless it is satisfied that`
  line `the warehouse in respect of which the application has been made has adequate facilities and safeguards`
  line `required to warehouse the goods of the nature specified in the application and the applicant satisfies the`
  line `financial, managerial and other eligibility criteria and competence as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no certificate of registration shall be refused to any applicant under this section unless`
  line `the applicant has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21040)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Registration of accreditation agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21040&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, from time to time, determine`
  line `the number of accreditation agencies as it may authorise to issue certificate of accreditation to warehouses`
  line `issuing negotiable warehouse receipts.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person fulfilling the qualifications and other requirements as may be prescribed and desirous`
  line `of functioning as an accreditation agency under this Act may make an application to the Authority`
  line `seeking its registration as such under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (2) shall be in such form and manner and shall be`
  line `accompanied by such fees and security deposit as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The form in which and the terms and conditions subject to which a certificate of registration as an`
  line `accreditation agency may be issued under this section shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21041)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liabilities of warehousemen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21041&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A warehouseman is liable for loss of, or injury to, goods`
  line `caused by his failure to exercise such care and diligence in regard to the goods as a careful and vigilant`
  line `owner of the goods of the same bulk, quality and value would exercise in the custody of them in similar`
  line conditions.
  line
  line `(2) In case the goods are damaged or lost in spite of taking all care and precautions by the`
  line `warehouseman due to unavoidable circumstances, the compensation equal to the value of goods at the`
  line `time of deposit of the goods shall be payable by the warehouseman.`
  line
  line `(3) In case the goods are damaged or lost due to the negligence of the warehouseman, then, the`
  line `compensation shall be equal to value of goods plus the loss of profit to the holder of the receipt.`
  line
  line `(4) The warehouseman shall not be responsible for any loss, destruction, damage or deterioration of`
  line `the goods delivered to him for storage attributable to circumstances such as force majeure, act of war, act`
  line `of public enemies and the like.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21042)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Duties of warehousemen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21042&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the absence of a lawful excuse, a warehouseman shall deliver`
  line `the goods referred to in a negotiable receipt, to the holder of the receipt on demand made by the holder`
  line `and on the holder fulfilling all the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) satisfying the warehouse lien;`
  line
  line `(b) surrendering the receipt in case of non-negotiable receipt and surrendering the receipt with`
  line `endorsements in case of negotiable receipt; and`
  line
  line `(c) acknowledging in writing the receipt of the goods.`
  line
  line `(2) If a warehouseman refuses or fails to deliver the goods in compliance with the provisions of this`
  line `section, the burden of proof shall lie on the warehouseman to establish the existence of a lawful excuse`
  line `for the refusal or failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21043)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duties of warehouseman to keep records and accounts of warehouse business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21043&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `warehouseman shall keep in a place of safety a complete and accurate set of records and accounts of all transactions pertaining to the operation of a warehouse including records and accounts of all goods`
  line `received in the warehouse and withdrawn there from, of all un issued receipts in his possession, of all`
  line `receipts issued, returned to, or cancelled, by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the warehouseman shall keep all the records and`
  line `accounts of the warehouse business in numerical sequence separate and distinct from the records and`
  line `accounts of any other business in such form and in such manner and for such period as the Authority may,`
  line `by regulations, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The warehouseman shall make available to the Authority for inspection the records and accounts`
  line `of the warehouse business at any time as may be desired by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21044)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Special powers of warehouseman to deal with perishable and hazardous goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21044&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `goods are of a perishable or hazardous nature, or their keeping shall deteriorate greatly in value or damage`
  line `other property, the warehouseman may give notice that is reasonable and possible under the`
  line `circumstances to the holder of the receipt for the goods, if the name and address of the holder is known to`
  line `the warehouseman or if not known to the warehouseman, then, to the depositor, requiring that person to`
  line `satisfy the lien on the goods and to remove them from the warehouse.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person to whom a notice under sub-section (1) is given, fails to satisfy the lien and remove`
  line `the goods within the time specified in the notice, the warehouseman may sell the goods at public or`
  line `private sale without advertising.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice referred to in sub-section (1) may be given by sending it by electronic mail, speed post`
  line `or registered post or telegraphically addressed to the person to whom it is to be given at the last known`
  line `address of the person and the notice is deemed to be given on the third day of the mailing.`
  line
  line `(4) If the warehouseman after a reasonable effort is unable to sell the goods, the warehouseman may`
  line `dispose of them in such other manner as he deems proper and shall incur no liability for that reason.`
  line
  line `(5) From the proceeds of any sale or disposal of goods made under this section, the warehouseman`
  line `shall, after satisfying his lien, hold the balance in trust for the holder of the receipt.`
  line
  line `(6) No notice shall be necessary if the warehouseman is satisfied on reasonable grounds that in the`
  line `circumstances of the case giving such notices is likely to cause further prejudice to the goods.`
  line
  line `(7) If, at any time, the warehouseman is satisfied that the quality of any fungible goods or any part`
  line `thereof has so deteriorated or is so deteriorating that it is necessary to do so, to protect the holders of`
  line `negotiable warehouse receipts from loss and time is not sufficient for him to seek their instructions, he`
  line `may, subject to the regulations in this behalf, dispose off the goods or any part thereof and keep the sale`
  line `proceeds after satisfying his lien in an escrow account for the benefit of the holders of receipts.`
  line
  line `(8) In case of disposal of fungible goods under sub-section (7), the warehouseman shall, at the choice`
  line `of the holder of the receipt, either pay the sale proceeds or deliver equivalent goods of the same grade,`
  line `quality and quantity to him.`
  line
  line `(9) Any endorsee shall have the right to intimate the address for service recorded with the`
  line warehouseman.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21045)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Lien of warehouseman on goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21045&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every warehouseman has a lien on goods deposited with`
  line `him for storage, whether deposited by the owner of the goods or by his authority, or by any person`
  line `entrusted with the possession of the goods by the owner or by his agent.`
  line
  line `(2) The lien of the warehouseman is for the amount of the storage and maintenance charges`
  line including--
  line
  line `(a) all lawful charges for storage and preservation of the goods;`
  line
  line `(b) all reasonable charges for--`
  line
  line `(i) any notice required to be given under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) notice and advertisement of sale;`
  line
  line `(iii) sale of goods where default is made in satisfying the lien of the warehouseman; and`
  line
  line `(iv) compliance of statutory provisions.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of any endorsement on the face of a negotiable warehouse receipt, by a bank or the`
  line `warehouseman, such endorsement shall be evidence of a pledge and the pledgee shall have priority over`
  line `the interest of the holder of the receipt.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of any pledge referred to in sub-section (3), the warehouseman shall not deliver the goods`
  line `unless the endorsement of the pledge has been duly got cancelled.`
  line
  line `(5) In case the goods are not taken back within the declared period of storage, the warehouseman`
  line `shall have the right to recover his charges, selling the goods by public auction, or in any other manner`
  line `provided in this section any goods upon which he has a lien.`
  line
  line `(6) The warehouseman shall give a notice in writing of his intention to sell the goods to the person`
  line `liable as debtor for the charges for which the lien exists or to the owner or person owning the right of`
  line `property of the goods.`
  line
  line `(7) The notice under sub-section (6) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) contain all the details about the goods, the location of warehouse, date of deposit, the name of`
  line `depositor and a statement of lien claimed by the warehouseman for the goods stored in the`
  line `warehouse; and`
  line
  line `(b) state that unless the charges are paid within the stipulated time mentioned in the notice, the`
  line `goods shall be advertised for sale and sold by public auction at a time and place as specified in the`
  line notice.
  line
  line `(8) If the charges are not paid on or before the day mentioned in the notice, then, unless any other`
  line `mode of sale is specified by the Authority, by regulations, an advertisement of the sale shall be published`
  line `in a leading newspaper having circulation in the locality where the sale is to be held as well as where the`
  line `owner of the goods is located and the sale shall be held not less than fourteen days from the date of first`
  line `publication of the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(9) The warehouseman shall, from the proceeds of the sale, satisfy his lien and shall pay over the`
  line `surplus, if any, to the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(10) If the surplus is not demanded by the person entitled thereto within ten days after the sale of`
  line `goods or if there are different claims, the warehouseman shall seek instructions from the Authority and`
  line `act as per the orders of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21046)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Warehouse receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21046&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) A warehouse receipt, which may be either in writing or in electronic`
  line `form, shall be a document of title to goods in writing if it contains all the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) receipt number;`
  line
  line `(b) warehouse registration number and date up to which it is valid;`
  line
  line `(c) name of the warehouse and its complete postal address;`
  line
  line `(d) name and address of the person by whom or on whose behalf the goods are deposited;`
  line
  line `(e) date of issue of the warehouse receipt;`
  line
  line `(f) statement that the goods received shall be delivered to the holder thereof, or that the goods`
  line `shall be delivered to the order of a named person;`
  line
  line `(g) rates of storage charges and handling charges;`
  line
  line `(h) description of the goods or of the packages containing them with particulars of quantity and`
  line `quality or grade;`
  line
  line `(i) market value of the goods at the time of deposit;`
  line
  line `(j) private marks of depositor on the goods or packages, if any, except in the case of fungible`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(k) name of the insurance company indemnifying for fire, flood, theft, burglary, misappropriation,`
  line `riots, strikes or terrorism;`
  line
  line `(l) whether the warehouse receipt is negotiable or non-negotiable;`
  line
  line `(m) statement of the amount of any advance made and of any liability incurred for which the`
  line `warehouseman claims his lien;`
  line
  line `(n) date and signature of the warehouseman or his authorised agent;`
  line
  line `(o) declared shelf-life of goods;`
  line
  line `(p) the fact that the warehouseman holds the lien on the goods deposited for his storage and`
  line `handling charges; and`
  line
  line `(q) that the receipt would be valid only till the date of expiry of declared shelf- life of the goods`
  line `for which it is issued.`
  line
  line `(2) In case a warehouseman wilfully omits from a negotiable warehouse receipt any of the particulars`
  line `set out in sub-section (1), he shall be liable for damages caused by such omission.`
  line
  line `(3) No warehouse receipt shall, by reason of the omission only of any of the particulars set-forth in`
  line `sub-section (1), be deemed to be invalid for the purpose of settlement of disputes or claims.`
  line
  line `(4) Authority may, with the prior approval of the Central Government, add, delete or modify any`
  line `particulars as specified in sub-clause (1) for all or any commodity or class of commodities or for any class`
  line `of warehouses.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21047)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Negotiability of warehouse receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21047&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The words in a negotiable warehouse receipt limiting`
  line `its negotiability shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) A warehouseman who issues a non-negotiable warehouse receipt shall cause to be plainly marked`
  line `upon its face the words "non-negotiable" or "not negotiable" in English or in the language in which it is`
  line issued.
  line
  line `(3) In case of non-compliance of sub-section (2), a holder of the warehouse receipt who purchases it`
  line `for valuable consideration believing it to be a negotiable warehouse receipt may, at his option, treat the`
  line `receipt as vesting in him all rights attaching to a negotiable warehouse receipt and imposing upon the`
  line `warehouseman the same liabilities which he would have incurred had the receipt been a negotiable`
  line `warehouse receipt and the warehouseman shall be liable accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) A negotiable warehouse receipt shall be valid for delivery till the date of expiry of the declared`
  line `shelf-life of the goods for which it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21048)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Negotiation of warehouse receipt by delivery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21048&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A negotiable warehouse receipt may be`
  line `negotiated by its delivery if, by the terms of the receipt, the warehouseman undertakes to deliver the`
  line `goods to the order of a named person, and that person or a subsequent endorsee has endorsed it.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21049)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Transfer of negotiable warehouse receipts without endorsement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21049&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where a negotiable receipt`
  line `is transferred for valuable consideration by delivery, and the endorsement of the transferor is essential for`
  line `negotiation, the transferee acquires a right against the transferor to compel him to endorse the receipt,`
  line `unless a contrary intention appears, and the negotiation takes effect as of the time when endorsement is`
  line made.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21050)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Warranties on negotiation of warehouse receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21050&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A person who, for valuable consideration,`
  line `negotiates a negotiable warehouse receipt by endorsement and delivery, including one who assigns for`
  line `valuable consideration, a claim secured by a receipt, unless a contrary intention appears, warrants the`
  line `following:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the receipt is genuine;`
  line
  line `(b) that the person has a legal right to negotiate or transfer it;`
  line
  line `(c) that the person has no knowledge of any fact that would impair the validity of the receipt;`
  line
  line `(d) that the person has a right to transfer the title to the goods; and`
  line
  line `(e) that the goods are merchantable or fit for a particular purpose when those warranties would`
  line `have been implied, if the contract of the parties had been to transfer without a receipt the goods`
  line `represented by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21051)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Non-liability of the endorser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21051&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The endorsement of a receipt does not make the endorser liable`
  line `for any failure on the part of the warehouseman or previous endorsers of the receipt to fulfil their`
  line `respective obligations.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21052)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Negotiation of warehouse receipt not impaired by fraud, mistake or duress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21052&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The validity of`
  line `the negotiation of a receipt is not impaired by the fact that--`
  line
  line `(a) the negotiation was a breach of duty on the part of the person making the negotiation; or`
  line
  line `(b) the owner of the receipt was induced by fraud, mistake or duress to entrust the possession or`
  line `custody of the receipt to that person, if the person to whom the receipt was negotiated or a person to`
  line `whom the receipt was subsequently negotiated, paid value for it without knowing of the breach of`
  line `duty, fraud, mistake or duress.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21053)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Subsequent negotiation of warehouse receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21053&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If a person having sold, mortgaged or pledged`
  line `goods that are in the custody of a warehouseman and for which a negotiable receipt has been issued,`
  line `continues in possession of the negotiable receipt, the subsequent negotiation of it by that person under any`
  line `sale or other disposition of the goods to any person receiving the receipt in good faith, for valuable`
  line `consideration and without notice of the previous sale, mortgage or pledge, has the same effect as if a`
  line `previous purchaser, mortgagee or pledgee of the goods, as the case may be, had expressly authorised the`
  line `subsequent negotiation.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (21054)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Delivery of goods to be made after due charges are paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21054&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `When a negotiable warehouse`
  line `receipt has been issued in respect of any goods, the warehouseman shall not deliver the goods to the`
  line `depositor or endorsee, until the due charges are paid to the custodian from the date of initial deposit till`
  line `delivery is made and the warehouse receipt is surrendered for cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (21055)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Transfer of non-negotiable receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21055&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) A non-negotiable warehouse receipt may be`
  line `transferred by the holder by delivery to a purchaser or donee of the goods in writing executed by the`
  line holder.
  line
  line `(2) A person to whom the goods covered by a non-negotiable warehouse receipt is transferred`
  line acquires--
  line
  line `(a) the title of the transferor to the goods; and`
  line
  line `(b) the right to deposit with the warehouseman the receipt or duplicate thereof or to give notice in`
  line `writing to the warehouseman of the transfer.`
  line
  line `(3) The transferee shall acquire the benefit of the obligation of the warehouseman to hold goods in`
  line `storage for him according to the terms of the receipt upon deposit of the transfer of the goods and on`
  line `giving notice in writing of the transfer and upon the warehouseman having a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `verifying the transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (21056)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Conclusiveness of negotiable warehouse receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21056&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `In the hands of a holder who has purchased`
  line `a negotiable warehouse receipt for valuable consideration, it shall be conclusive evidence of the goods`
  line `described in it as against the warehouseman or any person claiming through him.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21057)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Presumption in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21057&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `In a dispute between an endorser of a negotiable warehouse`
  line `receipt and his endorsee unless it is proved otherwise, it shall be presumed that--`
  line
  line `(a) the endorsement has been made voluntarily;`
  line
  line `(b) the endorsement has been made for full consideration;`
  line
  line `(c) the endorser had full legal title in the goods represented by the receipt; and`
  line
  line `(d) the endorsement has extinguished all the rights, title and interest of the endorser in the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21058)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Issue of duplicate receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21058&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No warehouseman shall issue a warehouse receipt without`
  line `actually receiving the goods of the quantity, quality or grade and other particulars as may be mentioned in`
  line `the receipt.`
  line
  line `(2) No warehouseman shall issue more than one receipt for the same goods deposited by any person:`
  line `Provided that in case of a loss or destruction, a duplicate receipt may be issued in such manner as may`
  line `be specified by the Authority by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) If a warehouseman fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (2), he would be liable for`
  line `all such damages caused by the failure to any person who has transacted on such receipt for valuable`
  line `consideration, believing it to be an original, even though the transaction is after the delivery of the goods`
  line `by the warehouseman to the holder of the original receipt.`
  line
  line `(4) A receipt on the face of which the word "duplicate" is plainly marked is a representation and`
  line `warranty by the warehouseman that it is an accurate copy of a receipt properly issued and uncancelled on`
  line `the date of issue of the duplicate warehouse receipt.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21059)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21059&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, there shall be constituted an authority to be`
  line `called the Warehousing Development and Regulatory Authority to exercise the powers conferred on, and`
  line `to perform the functions assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Authority shall be at New Delhi and the Authority may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, establish offices at other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (21060)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Composition of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21060&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(b) not more than two other members,`
  line
  line `to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of ability, integrity and standing who`
  line `have wide knowledge and experience in inventory management, insurance, preservation, quality control,`
  line `agriculture banking, finance, economics, law or administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (21061)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Tenure of office of Chairperson and other members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21061&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and every other`
  line `member shall hold office for a term not exceeding five years from the date on which he enters upon his`
  line `office and shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Chairperson or other member after he has attained the`
  line `age of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a member may--`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the Central Government notice of not less than`
  line `three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (21062)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Removal from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21062&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may remove from office any member`
  line who--
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuation in office detrimental to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) No such member shall be removed under clause (d) or clause (e) of sub-section (1) unless he has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (21063)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of Chairperson and other members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21063&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules as may be made in this behalf, the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms`
  line `and conditions of service of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson shall be the same as that of a Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(b) the other members of the Authority shall be the same as that of Joint Secretaries to the`
  line `Government of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (21064)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Bar on future employment of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21064&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson and the other members shall not, for`
  line `a period of two years from the date on which they cease to hold office as such, except with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, accept any employment in any concern in the warehousing sector.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (21065)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Chairperson to be the chief executive of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21065&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall be the chief`
  line `executive of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (21066)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Meetings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21066&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at such`
  line `meetings) as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, or if, for any reason he is unable to attend a meeting of the Authority, any other`
  line `member chosen by the members present from amongst themselves at the meeting shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes by the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson, or`
  line `the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (21067)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21067&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (21068)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Officers and employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21068&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may appoint officers and such other`
  line `employees as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its function under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Authority appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be governed by regulations made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (21069)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Warehousing Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21069&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, by notification, constitute a`
  line `Committee to be known as the Warehousing Advisory Committee to advise the Authority on matters`
  line `relating to the making of regulations under section 51 and make recommendations for effective`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Warehousing Advisory Committee shall consist of not more than fifteen members excluding`
  line `the members of the Authority to represent the interests of commerce, industry, engineering, agriculture,`
  line `consumers, organisations engaged in warehousing, quality control, preservation and research bodies.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Warehousing Advisory Committee may`
  line `advise the Authority on such other matters as may be referred to it by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (21070)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers and functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21070&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Authority shall have the duty to regulate and ensure implementation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act and promote orderly growth of the warehousing business.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the powers and functions of the`
  line `Authority shall include the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to issue to the applicants fulfilling the requirements for warehousemen a certificate of`
  line `registration in respect of warehouses, or renew, modify, withdraw, suspend or cancel such`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(b) to regulate the registration and functioning of accreditation agency, renew, modify, withdraw,`
  line `suspend or cancel such registration, and specify the code of conduct for officials of accreditation`
  line `agencies for accreditation of the warehouses;`
  line
  line `(c) to specify the qualifications, code of conduct and practical training for warehousemen and`
  line `staff engaged in warehousing business;`
  line
  line `(d) to regulate the process of pledge, creation of charges and enforcement thereof in respect of`
  line `goods deposited with the warehouse;`
  line
  line `(e) to promote efficiency in conduct of warehouse business;`
  line
  line `(f) to make regulations laying down the standards for approval of certifying agencies for grading`
  line `of goods;`
  line
  line `(g) to promote professional organisations connected with the warehousing business;`
  line
  line `(h) to determine the rate of, and levy, the fees and other charges for carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) to call for information from, undertaking inspection of, conducting enquiries and investigation`
  line `including audit of the warehouses, accreditation agencies and other organisations connected with the`
  line `warehousing business;`
  line
  line `(j) to regulate the rates, advantages, terms and conditions that may be offered by warehousemen`
  line `in respect of warehousing business;`
  line
  line `(k) to specify, by regulations, the form and manner in which books of account shall be maintained`
  line `and statement of accounts shall be rendered by warehousemen;`
  line
  line `(l) to maintain a panel of arbitrators and to nominate arbitrators from such panel in disputes`
  line `between warehouses and warehouse receipt holders;`
  line
  line `(m) to regulate and develop electronic system of holding and transfer of credit balances of`
  line `fungible goods deposited in the warehouses;`
  line
  line `(n) to determine the minimum percentage of space to be kept reserved for storage of agricultural`
  line `commodities in a registered warehouse;`
  line
  line `(o) to specify the duties and responsibilities of the warehouseman;`
  line
  line `(p) to exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (21071)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21071&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Authority grants of such sums of money as the`
  line `Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (21072)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Constitution of fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21072&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the Warehousing`
  line `Development and Regulatory Authority Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all Central Government grants, fees and charges received by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Authority from such other source as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums realised by way of penalties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other employees`
  line `of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) the other expenses of the Authority in connection with the discharge of its functions and for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (21073)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21073&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Authority shall have the same rights, privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books of account, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (21074)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Furnishing of returns, Annual Report, etc., to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21074&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall`
  line `furnish to the Central Government at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed, or as`
  line `the Central Government may direct to furnish such returns, statements and other particulars in regard to`
  line `any proposed or existing programme for the promotion and development of the warehousing industry as`
  line `the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Authority shall, within nine months`
  line `after the close of each financial year, submit to the Central Government an Annual Report giving a true`
  line `and full account of its activities including the activities for promotion and development of the`
  line `warehousing business during the previous financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of the reports received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be after they are`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (21075)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Powers of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21075&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in exercise of its powers and performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy, other than those relating to technical`
  line `and administrative matters, as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (21076)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21076&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that, on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Authority, it is unable to discharge`
  line `the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial`
  line `position of the Authority or the administration of the Authority has suffered; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification and for reasons to be specified therein, supersede the Authority for`
  line `such period not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification and nominate a person`
  line `to look after the functions of the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Authority to make representations against the proposed supersession`
  line `and shall consider the representation, if any, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson and other members shall, as from the date of supersession, be deemed to have`
  line `vacated their offices;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the person nominated by the Central`
  line `Government under clause (c) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government shall reconstitute the Authority by a fresh appointment of its`
  line `Chairperson and other members and in such case any person who had vacated his office under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a copy of the notification issued under sub-section (1) and a`
  line `full report of any action to be laid before each House of Parliament at the earliest.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law or in any contract or memorandum or articles of`
  line `association, on the removal of a person, from office under this section, that person shall not be entitled to`
  line `claim any compensation for the loss or termination of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (21077)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Appeals to Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21077&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Authority made`
  line `under this Act, or any rules or the regulations made thereunder may prefer an appeal to such person or authority appointed by the Central Government (hereafter referred to as the Appellate Authority) within`
  line `sixty days from the date of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the said period of sixty days but not`
  line `beyond a total period of ninety days if the appellant satisfies the Appellate Authority that he had sufficient`
  line `cause for not preferring the appeal within the said period.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal made under this section shall be made in such form and manner and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disposing of an appeal, the appellant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal filed before the Appellate Authority shall be heard and disposed of as expeditiously as`
  line `possible and endeavour shall be made to finally dispose of the appeal within a period of ninety days from`
  line `the date of its filing.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (21078)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21078&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any warehouseman knowingly issuing a negotiable warehouse`
  line `receipt without taking the actual physical delivery of the goods in his warehouse or a warehouseman or an`
  line `agent or servant of the warehouseman who issues a warehouse receipt without reasonably satisfying`
  line `himself that the goods for which such warehouse receipt is issued have actually been received or the`
  line `number, weight or grade of the goods corresponds to the number, weight or grade specified in the`
  line `warehouse receipt or the goods are under his actual control at the time of issuing such warehouse receipt,`
  line `commits an offence and shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years or with fine which may extend to four times the value of the goods or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) A warehouseman or an agent or servant of the warehouseman, who knowingly issues a duplicate`
  line `negotiable warehouse receipt without substantially following the procedure for the issue of a duplicate`
  line `warehouse receipt, commits an offence and shall be punishable for such offence with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) A warehouseman or an agent or servant of the warehouseman, who, knowingly that the negotiable`
  line `warehouse receipt in respect of such goods is outstanding and is uncancelled, delivers the goods without`
  line `obtaining possession of such negotiable warehouse receipt at or before the time of such delivery and`
  line `thereby causes unlawful loss or gain to any person, commits an offence and shall be punishable for such`
  line `an offence by imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) A warehouseman who fails, on surrender of a negotiable warehouse receipt by the depositor or`
  line `endorsee and payment of all his lawful charges and cancellation of encumbrances endorsed on the receipt,`
  line `within the declared shelf-life of the goods, as mentioned therein to deliver the goods represented by the`
  line `receipt commits an offence and shall be punishable for such offence with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to three times the value of the goods or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(5) Any depositor, who declared as the value of the goods delivered by him for storage with a`
  line `warehouseman an amount which he does not believe to be the proper value, commits an offence and shall`
  line `be punishable for such an offence with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (21079)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21079&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Chapter is committed by a company,`
  line `every person, who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of the company or was`
  line `responsible for making the deposit, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to punishment`
  line `if he proves that the contravention took place without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence`
  line `to prevent such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Chapter has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that such an offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager,`
  line `secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (21080)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Cognizance of offences by courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21080&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act, save on a complaint made by the Authority or by any officer authorised in`
  line `writing in this behalf by the authority.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (21081)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Chairperson, members, officers and other employees of Authority to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21081&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, members, officers and other employees of Authority and Appellate Authority shall be`
  line `deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public`
  line `servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (21082)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21082&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or any officer of the Central Government or any member, officer or`
  line `other employee of the Authority for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this Act or the rules or regulations made there under:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this Act shall exempt any person any suit or other proceedings which might,`
  line `apart from this Act, be brought against him.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (21083)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21083&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to`
  line `the Chairperson or any other member or officer of the Authority subject to such conditions, if any, as may`
  line `be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions (excluding the power to make regulations under`
  line `section 51) under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (21084)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Exemption from tax on wealth and income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21084&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) or any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force relating to tax on wealth, income, profits or gains, the Authority shall not be liable to`
  line `pay wealth-tax, income-tax or any other tax in respect of their wealth, income, profits or gains derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (21085)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21085&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which an application for obtaining a certificate of registration for`
  line `commencing or carrying on the business of warehousing issuing negotiable warehouse receipts may`
  line `be made and the fees which shall accompany such application under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which a certificate for registration of warehouses may be issued under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the financial, managerial and other eligibility criteria and competence which an applicant for`
  line `registration of warehouses shall satisfy under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the qualification and other requirements which a person applying for functioning as an`
  line `accreditation agency shall fulfill under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which an application for registration as an accreditation agency may`
  line `be made and the fees which shall accompany such application under sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) the form of certificate of registration of accreditation agency under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(g) the salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson and other members under section 28;`
  line
  line `(h) such other powers that may be exercised by the Authority under clause (p) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 35;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner of maintenance of annual statement of accounts to be maintained by the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner in which and the time within which returns and statements and`
  line `particulars are to be furnished by the Authority to the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 39;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and the manner in which an appeal may be made to the Appellate Authority and the`
  line `fee which shall accompany such appeal under sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure to be followed by the Appellate Authority in disposing of an appeal under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which`
  line `provision is to be or may be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (21086)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21086&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, with the previous approval`
  line `of the Central Government, and in consultation with the Warehousing Advisory Committee, by`
  line `notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the matters regulating the authorities of accreditation agencies under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner and the period for which a warehouseman shall keep the records and`
  line `accounts of the warehousing business under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of disposal of goods or any part thereof and the keeping of sale proceeds in an`
  line `escrow account by the warehouseman under sub-section (7) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the mode of sale under sub-section (10) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of issuance of duplicate warehouse receipt under the proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) the time and places of meetings of the Authority and the procedure to be followed at such`
  line `meetings including the quorum necessary for the transaction of business under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31;`
  line
  line `(g) the terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(h) the registration and functioning of accreditation agencies, renewal, modification, withdrawal,`
  line `suspension or cancellation of such registration and the code of conduct for officials of accreditation`
  line `agencies for accreditation of the warehouses under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(i) the standards for approval of certifying agencies for grading of goods under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(j) the rate of fees and other charges to be levied for carrying out the provisions of this Act under`
  line `clause (h) of sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be or may be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (21087)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21087&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government and every regulation made by the Authority under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should`
  line `not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (21088)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21088&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (21089)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21089&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (21090)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Amendment of Act 2 of 1899.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670&sectionId=21090&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00009_200737_1517807325670
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `After section 8B of the Stamp Act, 1899, the following section`
  line `shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"8C. Negotiable warehouse receipts not liable to stamp duty.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, negotiable warehouse receipts shall not be liable to stamp duty."`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
